eateries.name: 104West!
eateries.about:
Located next to the Center for Jewish Living building on the south edge of west campus, 104West! is Cornell's kosher and multicultural dining room. Menus are prepared under the supervision of STAR-K (meat and pareve) and STAR-D (dairy) Kosher Certifications, and Jewish dietary laws are strictly followed with the direction of a resident "Mashgiach," or kosher-food supervisor.

You don't have to keep kosher to enjoy the menuâ€“come sample traditional kosher entrees and enjoy mouth-watering ethnic and international options with a kosher flair. Dining options also include Halal, Seventh-day Adventist, vegetarian, vegan, and other diets.

Shabbat dinner times vary over the course of the year, based on sunset times. Save money and help us plan by making advance reservations for Shabbat dinners and holiday meals at https://kosher.scl.cornell.edu!

More Info: 104West!
eateries.aboutshort: Cornell's kosher and multicultural dining room is STAR-K and STAR-D certified.

eateries.name: McCormick's Restaurant
eateries.about:
McCormick's Restaurant at Moakley House offers a casual environment close to campus, open Monday through Saturday during the golf season. Named for Jack McCormick, a varsity golfer from the Cornell Class of 1957, this eatery alongside the award-winning Robert Trent Jones Golf Course at Cornell University isn't just for golfers. It's open to the public and has plenty of parking, and we welcome everyone for a drink, snack, or meal. Join us for some great food and stellar views of the green!

Note: McCormick's has limited service available on Sundays.

More Info: McCormick's at Moakley House
